  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6773.29 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6765 (-19.4B) and max positive gamma at 6780 (+23.5B), dealers are currently in neutral hedging mode but approaching the key resistance zone. The PIN regime suggests dealers will aggressively sell any push toward 6780 and provide support on dips toward 6765, creating a tight trading range with mean-reverting behavior. The recent GEX surge combined with the flip strike just above at 6797 indicates heavy options positioning that should cap upside momentum and create resistance layers every 5 points higher.\n\nKey levels: 6765 (major support/dealer buying), 6780 (major resistance/dealer selling), and 6797 (regime flip).\n\n**Bottom line: expect price to ping-pong between 6765-6780 with limited breakout potential.**",
